{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01926/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01926"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:19:26"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["establishing shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A dimly-lit kitchen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01926","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01926"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1/0fcc8807-9f25-4162-bfae-edaca63084f1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:13:19.563Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds’s house is introduced through a series of static shots in cool lighting. It almost resembles a dungeon at times: sterile, cold, dusty. It lacks the vibrancy that Alma prefers and represents the “dead house” that Reynolds will later acknowledge the House of Woodcock has become without any changes. In this setting, Alma stands out even more in her red dress. She is not of this world.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:877.9955947136564,273.53524229074884,826.1453744493392,410.4185022026432"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1/1a955b8c-f777-4a2c-abf3-64b6cf1856ab","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:13:29.484Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Jonny Greenwood’s score, here replete with pensive strings and gentle piano, adds, to borrow Reynolds’s words, the “spooky” atmosphere of Alma’s introduction to the country estate. It is filmed like a barren castle where Reynolds’s secrets are kept.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01926/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:10.825991189427349,39.28414096916292,196.07929515418493,133.17180616740092"}}}]}]}]}